climate.description:
Select climate devices that will be controlled by this integration.

**Global Pool**: These devices form the default pool. You can later create specific bindings that target only certain devices.

**Tip**: It's okay to leave this empty and configure device targeting in bindings instead.

Selected calendars: {calendar_entities}
Available climate devices: {climate_count}

options.description:
Configure basic operational settings. You can change these later in the integration options.

**Dry Run Mode**: Enable this to test your configuration without actually changing climate device states.

**Debug Mode**: Enable verbose logging for troubleshooting.

Calendars: {calendar_entities}
Climate devices: {climate_count}

init.description:
Manage all aspects of your Climate Control Calendar integration.

**Current Configuration:**
• Calendars: {calendar_count}
• Climate Devices: {climate_count}
• Slots: {slot_count}
• Bindings: {binding_count}

Select a configuration area to manage:

edit_slot.description:
Select a slot to modify.

Current slots: {slot_count}

**Tip**: Use YAML Editor for bulk operations.

edit_slot_detail.description:
Modify slot settings.

**Slot ID**: {slot_id}
**Bindings using this slot**: {binding_count}

**Warning**: Changes affect all bindings that use this slot.

delete_slot.description:
Select a slot to remove.

**Warning**: Bindings referencing this slot will fail until reconfigured.

Current slots: {slot_count}

